==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*nasiz'', from Indo-European ''*nas-''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[nose]], Middle Dutch [[nose|nōse]] (Dutch [[neus]]), Old High German [[nasa]] (German [[Nase]]), Old Norse [[nǫs]] (Swedish [[nos]]).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Latin [[naris|nāris]], Sanskrit [[नस्]], Russian [[нос]], Lithuanian [[nosis|nósis]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'nozʊ/

